<h1>Indian Seasons</h1>
<p style="color:darkred;font-size:24px;font-weight:bold;text-align:center;">
India experiences six major seasons, each bringing unique weather,
        festivals, crops, and natural beauty.
</p>
<div class="intro">
<h3>About Indian Seasons</h3>
<p>
            India's climate is diverse due to its geographical location.
            The year is traditionally divided into six seasons known as
            Vasant (Spring), Grishma (Summer), Varsha (Monsoon),
            Sharad (Autumn), Hemant (Pre-Winter), and Shishir (Winter).
            These seasons influence agriculture, festivals, tourism,
            and daily life across the country.
        </p>
    </div>
<div class="main-container">

<h2 align="center">🇮🇳 Incredible India and Its Seasons 🇮🇳</h2>

<p>
India is a land of diverse climates and landscapes. From the snowy
Himalayas in the north to the tropical beaches in the south,
different regions experience seasons in unique ways. Indian seasons
play a vital role in agriculture, tourism, festivals, and daily life.
</p>

<p>
The Indian Meteorological Department generally recognizes four major
seasons, while traditional Indian culture recognizes six seasons.
These seasons influence crop production, water resources, and
celebrations across the country.
</p>
<div class="season-container">
<div class="season spring">
<h2>Spring</h2>
<img src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1520763185298-1b434c919102?w=600"
     alt="Spring Season"
     class="season-img">
<p><b>Months:</b> February - March</p>
            <p>
                Spring is known as the king of seasons. Flowers bloom,
                trees become green, and the weather remains pleasant.
            </p>
</div>
<div class="season summer">
<img src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1507525428034-b723cf961d3e?w=300"
     alt="Summer" class="season-img">

<h2>☀ Summer</h2>
            <p><b>Months:</b> April - June</p>
            <p>
                Summer is hot and dry. People enjoy cold drinks,
                mangoes, ice cream, and vacations.
            </p>
</div>
<div class="season monsoon">
<img src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1515694346937-94d85e41e6f0?w=300"
     alt="Monsoon" class="season-img">
 <h2>🌧 Monsoon</h2>
            <p><b>Months:</b> June - September</p>
            <p>
                Monsoon brings rainfall that is essential for agriculture.
                Rivers and lakes become full during this season.
            </p>
        </div>
<div class="season autumn">
<img src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1506744038136-46273834b3fb?w=300"
